title: For Sale:  FRENCH Antique “ZAOUE” Percussion Smooth “Rifle”
postcontent: FRENCH Antique “ZAOUE” Percussion Smooth “Rifle”Finely Engraved, Made in Marseille, France Circa 1860Here we present an antique Percussion Smooth Bore “Rifle”, made circa 1860 by “Zaoue”, a gunmaker of Marseille, France. Other guns have been found with his maker’s mark, ranging from percussion double guns to pinfire revolvers. All of these bear his mark, and most are finely engraved, suggesting that he was dealing in higher end firearms.This short and handy firearm features a smooth, .67 caliber bore, but there are a front blade sight and tangent-style adjustable rear sight present. Barrel is 27-3/8 inches in length, round and with a rib on top. The barrel has a very nice damascened pattern. Smooth bores are quite versatile in function and ammunition, as well as much simpler to manufacture than rifled barrels. The gun also features sling swivels on the butt and the second ramrod holder. The engraving features several hunting dogs, one on the barrel tang, one on the lock plate, and an engraving of a tiger on the trigger guard. The lock is also marked “ZAOUE” and inlaid in gold.The overall condition of this piece is very good. The barrel has turned an even brown over time. The engraving is well done. The markings are clear and legible. The stock is well fit and solid. The bore is smooth and in good condition. The lock is strong.Own the original! This is a legitimate antique and not a reproduction.Barrel is 27-3/8 inches in length.Caliber: .67 percussionOverall condition as seen in photos.

title: For Sale:  Lake City .300 AAC BLK Brass (250ct)
postcontent: This is fully processed .300 AAC Blackout brass made from Lake City (LC) military 5.56 once-fired brass. The process starts with the brass being sorted to ensure LC is all that is used, then the brass is cleaned to remove any dirt, carbon, or grease. This ensures that there are no obstructions on or in the brass that can interfere with sizing and trimming. On a Dillon Precision Machine each case is deprimed using a Dillon Universal Decapping die, then primer pockets are swaged and uniformed removing the military crimp and ensuring the primer pockets are not over sized. Next, each case is sized and trimmed on a Dillon RT1500 well within SAMMI specifications of 1.368 -.020 (1.348 to 1.368) which will allow you to reload several times before needing to trim. Next, the overall dimensions are checked with a precision case gauge and calipers to ensure maximum quality. Approximately once every 20 - 30 cases processed are sampled to maintain integrity of the specifications. Next, the flash holes of each case are de-burred and inspected to ensure there are no mixed head stamps. Next, the brass is cleaned in a wet tumbler with stainless steel media ensuring each case is cleaned inside and out.As this is "once-fired" brass, some cases my exhibit minor dents from previous firing, however, I do my best to remove all cases that do not have a like-new appearance. To accommodate for anything I might have missed I will always include additional cases.Cash, money order, or bank check. Add $8.00 if you want it shipped. Thank you for looking.

title: For Sale:  German Mauser K-98 Nazi Luftwaffe Rifle 1939 k98k k43 g43 g-43 k98 k-43 k98 98k
postcontent: This is a Nazi German Luftwafffe Mauser K98 code 42, 1939 manufactured buy Mauser Werke AG, Oberndorf, Germany. This Luftwaffe rifle is serial numbered 2889i. All numbers are matching except the front band E/655 (7313) and cleaning rod (64). The band spring is not numbered and is proofed mark E/26.The bolt and all its parts are numbered to the rifle. The bore is bright and shinny. There is some very, very slight corrosion on a few areas of the rifling which may come off with a good cleaning. The bore is stamped 7.9 on the barrel and my 7.92 bore gauge will not enter the bore due to very little wear. I would rate the bore as excellent. For a combat rifle the stock is in excellent condition with only some minor dings and scratched. The stock and hand guard have never been refinished or messed with in any way. The light walnut stocks are extremely hard to come by. The stock and hand guard are numbered to the rifle in the barrel channels and on the bottom of the butt area of the stock. The stock and hand guard have E/63 proof marks which can be clearly seen. The blueing has worn thin in places as can be seen in the photos, but still remains very strong over almost all of the rifle. The trigger guard and floor plate are machined and proof marked E/63. The butt plate is stamped E/63 and has the serial number. The rear bands is numbered to the rifle and E/63. The original sling has an Eagle ink stamp proof mark and the manufacturers stamp imbedded into the leather. I can only make out the name “RUDOLPH” in the stamping. The frog also has a manufactures stamp and I can only make out SEIBOU “62”. The rear sight is number to the rifle. The cleaning rod is an original WW2 10” issue. This rifle came directly from the veterans family many years ago. This is an excellent collector grade example of a pre-war German Luftwaffe rifle that will enhance any collection. It is very hard to find one in this condition. This sale must be to a FFL dealer or C&R license holder without exception. Payment of a postal money order or bank cashiers check must be received in 10 days of auction closing. Shipping and insurance will cost an additional $45.00. This firearm is being sold as a collector item only. As with alI curious and relics firearms I advise that a qualified and certified gun smith inspect this rifle prior to firing it at your own risk. A three day non fire inspection period from the date received will be granted. If the rifle is returned in the allotted time and in exactly the same condition as sent a refund will be returned less shipping and handling.
